# FloLabs design guide (required)

Source: `AI Design and Coding Guide.md` and tokens in `app/globals.css`.

## Content (§1)

- Preserve user-pasted copy exactly; do not rewrite without explicit approval.
- No em-dashes (—); use commas or colons.
- Spell project names correctly: FloLabs, CAIPO, FloBrain, MoodChanger, Hephaestus, Flo Chronos.
- Simple, clear language; short button labels; no invented product claims.

## Layout (§4–§5)

- Use `Container`, `Section`, `Col`, `ContentColumn` from `@/components/layout/*`.
- Grid: 4 cols mobile (320–767px), 8 cols tablet (768–1023px), 12 cols desktop (1024px+).
- Center in `--max-width-content` (90rem); verify 1440px+ large desktop.
- Fluid containers; no fixed widths that cause horizontal scroll; images scale in parents.
- Check mobile, tablet, and desktop for every section.

## Spacing & components (§7–§8)

- Use spacing tokens (`--spacing-section-y*`, `--spacing-card`, `--spacing-gutter-*`).
- Reuse `Button`, `Card`, `lib/ui-styles`, and `components/ui/*`; avoid one-off styles.
- Interactive elements: `--min-touch-target` (44px). Cards/buttons use `--radius-*` tokens.

## Design & theme (§3, §10)

- Clean, professional layouts; no random gradients, neon glows, or generic AI aesthetics.
- Full light/dark support via semantic color tokens; readable text and visible borders in both.

## Typography (§6)

- Presentation type scale from Version 3.pdf — see `.cursor/rules/typography.mdc`.
- Headings use `text-balance`; prevent orphan words on headings and CTAs.

## Assets & SEO (§9, §11)

- `public/logo.svg` in header and as favicon (`currentColor`, both themes).
- OG/Twitter meta with `siteImages.heroBackground` (`public/images/hero-background.webp`). Consistent icon sizes and image framing.

## Before finishing (§13)

- No overflow, orphan words, or theme flash on reload.
- Header, footer, buttons, and forms match global component styles.
